  <section>
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para>XHTML5 is an XML-based <quote>concrete syntax</quote> of the HTML5
    <quote>abstract language</quote> (the <quote>World Wide Web's markup
    language</quote>). It is served using the
    <computeroutput>application/xhtml+xml</computeroutput> Internet media
    type.<xref linkend="xhtml5-html5" /></para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>XHTML5</title>

    <para>XHTML5 is used to describe a user-friendly rendering of the object,
    optionally with images, icons, javascript, etc. embedded. It is also
    marked up with RDFa attributes so as it is also machine readable.</para>

    <para>Pages are typically either lists of resources (e.g.
    <computeroutput>&lt;ul&gt;</computeroutput>,
    <computeroutput>&lt;ol&gt;</computeroutput>,
    <computeroutput>&lt;tr&gt;</computeroutput> etc.) or a rendering of an
    individual resource.</para>

